This recalls Rene Guenon mentioning how Abraham submits to Melchizedek because Melchizedek uses the name "Most High" for God, while Abraham uses the name "All-Powerful" for Him instead. The first name represents a superior "divine aspect", thus Melchizedek is superior to Abraham.

Gene Wolfe joked that instead of asking someone what his religion is and the name of his deity, you should ask him to describe his theological beliefs and his deity's qualities. But in Hebrew as a sacred language there is full overlap between name and theology.
Finally, the Eucharistic Christian priesthood is in the office of Melchizedek.
